<subSubSection id="C36DC682FFB6FFACF0F2FC065150E8DF" pageId="24" pageNumber="525" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC89509FFB6FFACF0F2FC065150E8DF" blockId="24.[151,1438,853,1526]" pageId="24" pageNumber="525">
<emphasis id="B903491BFFB6FFACF0F2FC0651E4EFFF" bold="true" box="[199,481,961,986]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="525" reason="1">Diagnostic description.</emphasis>
Antenna 1 flagellum article 1 lacking robust seta on distal margin; accessory flagellum forming cap. Antenna 2 flagellum articles 3–5 slender in female, article 3 enlarged in male; articles 3–5 with brush setae on the anterior margin. Mandibular incisor curved; molar a reduced column with convex triturating surface or proximally setose and distally triturating; palp attached midway. Maxilla 1 ST-7 serrate along the distomedial medial margin; ST-D slender, apically cuspidate. Maxilliped outer plate apical robust setae present. Gnathopod 1 subchelate; coxa slightly to greatly shorter than coxa 2, tapering distally; carpus slightly longer than propodus; propodus palm acute, straight. Pereopod 4 coxa with well developed posteroventral lobe. Uropod 2 inner ramus constricted. Uropod 3 rami plumose setae absent in female, present occasionally in adult male. 
<taxonomicName id="4C77EE8AFFB6FFACF567FB7A5599E8F3" authorityName="Pearse" authorityYear="1952" box="[1362,1436,1213,1238]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Telsidae" genus="Telson" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilostomatoida" pageId="24" pageNumber="534" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Telson</taxonomicName>
moderately cleft.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36DC682FFB6FFACF0F2FAC25564E9F7" pageId="24" pageNumber="525" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC89509FFB6FFACF0F2FAC25564E9F7" blockId="24.[151,1438,853,1526]" pageId="24" pageNumber="525">
<emphasis id="B903491BFFB6FFACF0F2FAC2513EE93B" bold="true" box="[199,315,1285,1310]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="525" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C77EE8AFFB6FFACF1F0FAC2524CE93B" authorityName="J. L. Barnard" authorityYear="1966" box="[453,585,1285,1310]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lysianassidae" genus="Thrombasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B903491BFFB6FFACF1F0FAC2524CE93B" box="[453,585,1285,1310]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="525">Thrombasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was established by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE6E8F8FFB6FFACF307FAC253D8E93B" author="Barnard, J. L." box="[818,989,1285,1310]" pageId="24" pageNumber="525" pagination="1 - 166" refId="ref22371" refString="Barnard, J. L. (1966) Submarine canyons of southern California. Part V. Systematics: Amphipoda. Allan Hancock Pacific Expeditions, 27, 1 - 166." type="journal article" year="1966">Barnard (1966)</bibRefCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName id="4C77EE8AFFB6FFACF427FAC15490E93B" authorityName="J. L. Barnard" authorityYear="1966" box="[1042,1173,1285,1310]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lysianassidae" genus="Thrombasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tracalero">
<emphasis id="B903491BFFB6FFACF427FAC15490E93B" box="[1042,1173,1285,1310]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="525">T. tracalero</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and was subsequently placed in the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="4C77EE8AFFB6FFACF1E7FAEE5251E967" authorityName="Norman" authorityYear="1900" box="[466,596,1321,1346]" class="Malacostraca" family="Uristidae" genus="Schisturella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B903491BFFB6FFACF1E7FAEE5251E967" box="[466,596,1321,1346]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="525">Schisturella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE6E8F8FFB6FFACF2B6FAEE53C4E967" author="Barnard, J. L. &amp; Karaman, G. S." box="[643,961,1321,1346]" pageId="24" pageNumber="525" pagination="1 - 866" refId="ref22580" refString="Barnard, J. L. &amp; Karaman, G. S. (1991) The families and genera of marine gammaridean Amphipoda (except marine gammaroids). Records of the Australian Museum, Supplement, 13, 1 - 866. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.3853 / j. 0812 - 7387.13.1991.367" type="journal article" year="1991">Barnard &amp; Karaman (1991)</bibRefCitation>
. However, we consider 
<taxonomicName id="4C77EE8AFFB6FFACF4E1FAEE555DE967" authorityName="J. L. Barnard" authorityYear="1966" box="[1236,1368,1321,1346]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lysianassidae" genus="Thrombasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B903491BFFB6FFACF4E1FAEE555DE967" box="[1236,1368,1321,1346]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="525">Thrombasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="4C77EE8AFFB6FFACF118FA8A51AAE943" authorityName="Norman" authorityYear="1900" box="[301,431,1357,1382]" class="Malacostraca" family="Uristidae" genus="Schisturella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B903491BFFB6FFACF118FA8A51AAE943" box="[301,431,1357,1382]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="525">Schisturella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the gnathopod 1 coxa, which is tapering and slightly reduced, not vestigial as in 
<emphasis id="B903491BFFB6FFACF0A2FAB65125E9AF" box="[151,288,1393,1418]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="525">
<taxonomicName id="4C77EE8AFFB6FFACF0A2FAB65118E9AF" authorityName="Norman" authorityYear="1900" box="[151,285,1393,1418]" class="Malacostraca" family="Uristidae" genus="Schisturella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Schisturella</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
There are four other genera in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C77EE8AFFB6FFACF2ACFAB652FAE9AF" authorityName="Boeck" authorityYear="1871" box="[665,767,1393,1418]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lysianassidae" genus="Tryphosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B903491BFFB6FFACF2ACFAB652FAE9AF" box="[665,767,1393,1418]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="525">Tryphosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group with a gnathopod 1 coxa that is not vestigial. Of these, 
<taxonomicName id="4C77EE8AFFB6FFACF0A2FA52511EE98B" authorityName="J. L. Barnard" authorityYear="1966" box="[151,283,1429,1454]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lysianassidae" genus="Thrombasia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B903491BFFB6FFACF0A2FA52511EE98B" box="[151,283,1429,1454]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="525">Thrombasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be separated from 
<taxonomicName id="4C77EE8AFFB6FFACF21AFA525297E98B" authorityName="Barnard &amp; Karaman" authorityYear="1991" box="[559,658,1429,1454]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lysianassidae" genus="Gronella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B903491BFFB6FFACF21AFA525297E98B" box="[559,658,1429,1454]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="525">Gronella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the gnathopod 1 carpus, which is longer than the propodus, from 
<taxonomicName id="4C77EE8AFFB6FFACF0A2FA7E50FBE9F7" authorityName="Boeck" authorityYear="1871" box="[151,254,1465,1490]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lysianassidae" genus="Tryphosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B903491BFFB6FFACF0A2FA7E50FBE9F7" box="[151,254,1465,1490]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="525">Tryphosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C77EE8AFFB6FFACF107FA7D5198E9F4" authorityName="Barnard &amp; Karaman" authorityYear="1987" box="[306,413,1466,1489]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lysianassidae" genus="Bruunosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B903491BFFB6FFACF107FA7D5198E9F4" box="[306,413,1466,1489]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="525">Bruunosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the tapering gnathopod 1 coxa, and from 
<taxonomicName id="4C77EE8AFFB6FFACF3B1FA7E5408E9F7" authorityName="Kilgallen &amp; Lowry" authorityYear="2014" box="[900,1037,1465,1490]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lysianassidae" genus="Glorieusella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="24" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B903491BFFB6FFACF3B1FA7E5408E9F7" box="[900,1037,1465,1490]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="525">Glorieusella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the subchelate gnathopod 1.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36DC682FFB6FFACF0F2FA1A530FE9D3" box="[199,778,1501,1526]" pageId="24" pageNumber="525" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BC89509FFB6FFACF0F2FA1A530FE9D3" blockId="24.[151,1438,853,1526]" box="[199,778,1501,1526]" pageId="24" pageNumber="525">
<emphasis id="B903491BFFB6FFACF0F2FA1A5165E9D3" bold="true" box="[199,352,1501,1526]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="525" reason="1">Distribution.</emphasis>
Pacific Ocean, South Atlantic Ocean.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
